- importing 
    from django.common import CommonMiddleware, BrokenLinkEmailsMiddleware

`CommonMiddleware`
----------------
- in `settings.MIDDLEWARE`

    MIDDLEWARE = [
        ...
        'django.middleware.common.CommonMiddleware',
        ...
    ]

- provided conveniences:

    - forbid access to user agents in `DISALLOWED_USER_AGENTS` (a list of regex objects)

    - performs url rewriting baed on the `APPEND_SLASH` and `PREPEND_WWW` settings

    - sets the "Content-length" header for non-streaming responses

- `CommonMiddleware.response_redirect_class` defaults to `HttpResponsePermanentRedirect`. To customize this, extend `CommonMiddleware` and override the attribute. 

`BrokenLinkEmailsMiddleware`
--------------------------
- sends broken link notification emails to the list in `settings.MANAGERS`. The list has the same format as `settings.ADMINS` and is specifically used to determine who receives these notifications.

    ADMINS = [('John', 'john@example.com'), ('Mary', 'mary@example.com')]

    MANAGERS = [('kim', 'kim@example.com'), ('david', 'david@example.com')]


